All Classes

  • Class Description
    Commands
    Contains the one character commands used in the console Tic-Tac-Toe.
    ComputerPlayer
    Interface for generating a move for the computer player.
    Coordinate
    Represents an immutable coordinate in a two dimensional system.
    Direction
    Represents an immutable direction in a two dimensional coordinate system.
    Directions
    Contains four different directions: Vertical, horizontal, diagonal and reverse diagonal
    GameBoard
    Represents a 2D game board that can be edited.
    GameBoardPrinter
    Used for printing a GameBoard to the console.
    GameState
    Represents the state of a Tic-Tac-Toe game.
    ImmutableGameBoard
    Represents a read-only 2D game board.
    MovePair
    Represents an immutable pair of moves made by the human player and the computer.
    RandomComputer
    A ComputerPlayer that generates random moves at available squares.
    SmartComputer
    A ComputerPlayer that tries to block the player and to make moves that are somewhat intelligent.
    TicTacToe
    A game of Tic-Tac-Toe played in the console.
    TicTacToe
    A game of Tic-Tac-Toe played with a GUI.
    TicTacToeGame
    A game of Tic-Tac-Toe where the size of the game board and the number of game pieces in a row needed to win can be set.
    Utils
    Contains various utility methods.
    VictoryChecker
    Used to check if a player has won the game with the last move they made.
